          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Small angle elastic scattering of neutrons by",
                " uranium at energies between 18 MeV and 120 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCY"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Harwell synchrocyclotron and polarized beam"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "PHOTO"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Proton beam on aluminum target, 3.8 cm thick,",
                " producing neutrons at 45 degrees to the proton beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EN-RSL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " - the overall energy resolution was obtained",
                " by combining the width of the energy band with the",
                " intrinsic energy resolution of the spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Natural uranium scatterer, 3.81 cm thick for",
                " all angles, and 2.55 cm thick for 1 degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight spectrometer, 27 m flight path."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Organic liquid scintillator counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Polarization calculated from observed asymmetries",
                " by least squares fit to the expression.",
                "   A(theta) = ( P(theta) + B*theta)p(1.)sin(alpha)",
                " where B*theta represents small angle nuclear",
                " polarizations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Corrected for multiple scattering of 15 to 19%",
                " and neutron detection efficiency and intensity.",
                " Because the cross-section for inelastic scattering at",
                " each energy and angle was very much smaller than the",
                " corresponding elastic cross-section, a somewhat crude",
                " estimate of the former was sufficient to enable the",
                " experim. results to be corrected without introducing",
                " appreciable errors. Corrections, which varied from",
                " 0.9 +- 0.5 b/sr at 18 MeV to 0.2+-0.1 b/sr at 120 MeV",
                " were deduced from measurements (see REF-REF) on the",
                " production of charged particles from neutron",
                " bombardment at 90 MeV and from measurements (see",
                " REF-REF) of inelastic neutron scattering at 14.5 MeV.",
                " Corrections for the electromagnetic scattering of",
                " neutrons were small, being 2.2, 0.54 and 0.16 b/sr at",
                " 1., 2.53 and 4.52 degr., respectively. These values",
                " are slightly energy dependent due to the finite size",
                " of the nucleus but the effects of this dependence are",
                " insignificant in comparison with the errors placed",
                " upon the nuclear cross-sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
